**Explanation:**  
A debounce function ensures a given function is only called after the specified delay has elapsed since the last time it was invoked.

```javascript
// Debounce function implementation
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function (...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example usage:
function onResize() {
  console.log('Window resized!');
}

window.addEventListener('resize', debounce(onResize, 300));
```

**In this example:**  
`onResize` will only log to the console once 300ms have passed since the user's last resize event.
